<h2>Archive Maze Sites</h2>
<p>Designed with Stanley Donwood. Each is a different era. Sites 5, 6, and 11 are dead (404).</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site1/">Site 1</a> - Pablo Honey era; "Get your fix here" links page naming the earliest fansites</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site2/">Site 2</a> - The Bends era; "This is the Radiohead internet site"</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site3/">Site 3</a> - OK Computer era; "a site by radiohead and stnly dnwd who is a confused man"</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site4/">Site 4</a> - Geocities-era earnestness; a sincere link lives somewhere in here</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site7/">Site 7</a> - Kid A era; links to Friends of the Earth, internet as activism</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site8/">Site 8</a> - Donwood labyrinth; corridors of dead links and half-remembered artwork</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site9/">Site 9</a> - HTTT era; Flash labyrinth linking to radiohead.tv and slowlydownward.com</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site10/">Site 10</a> - "TEMPORARY RESTRAINING ORDER." One page. Deliberately minimal.</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site12/">Site 12</a> - In Rainbows era; "the official website where we put things" + Dead Air Space</li>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site13/">Site 13</a> ★ - "meaningless series of loops, discarded ephemera" - start here</li>
</ul>

<h2>Scrapbooks, Blogs &amp; Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://archive.radiohead.com/Site12/deadairspace/">Dead Air Space</a> - Thom Yorke's blog, In Rainbows / TKOL era</li>
  <li><a href="https://radiohead.com/library">Diet of Worms</a> - 2004 scrapbook via Public Library Memory Hole; Burn the Witch draft was in here</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.slowlydownward.com/">Stanley Donwood - Slowly Downward</a> - Donwood's actual site; artwork, archive, woefully out of date by design</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.instagram.com/stanleydonwood">Stanley Donwood - Instagram</a> - process work, new prints, worth following on its own</li>
</ul>

<h2>Fan Sites &amp; Deep Archives</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://citizeninsane.eu/">Citizen Insane</a> - exhaustive database, all albums + solo projects, est. 2006, still actively updated ✅</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.greenplastic.info/">Green Plastic Radiohead</a> - oldest US fansite, est. 1997, frozen ~2012, deliberately preserved ✅</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.greenplastic.info/cold-storage/">Green Plastic Cold Storage</a> - print articles, fan art, Ed's diary, facsimile of lost site "Lift" ✅</li>
  <li><a href="https://ateaseweb.com/">At Ease</a> - long-running news + live archive; board died Aug 2024, news pages still up ⚠️</li>
  <li><a href="https://wastecentral.ning.com/">W.A.S.T.E. Central</a> - semi-official Ning fan community; decayed, accounts mostly inaccessible ⚠️</li>
  <li><a href="https://the-radiohead-almanac.fandom.com/wiki/The_Radiohead_Almanac_Wiki">Radiohead Almanac</a> - fan wiki cataloguing every known live recording ✅</li>
</ul>

