</ul>

<h2>The Music - A Way In</h2>
<p>Albums in release order. Start with OK Computer or In Rainbows, not Pablo Honey.</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pablo_Honey">Pablo Honey</a> - 1993; origin point, not the entry point</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Bends_(album)">The Bends</a> - 1995; last guitar album; gateway for many</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OK_Computer">OK Computer</a> - 1997; essential</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kid_A">Kid A</a> - 2000; essential</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amnesiac_(album)">Amnesiac</a> - 2001; essential</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hail_to_the_Thief">Hail to the Thief</a> - 2003; underrated</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In_Rainbows">In Rainbows</a> - 2007; essential; pay what you want changed everything</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_King_of_Limbs">The King of Limbs</a> - 2011; live versions better than studio</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Moon_Shaped_Pool">A Moon Shaped Pool</a> - 2016; essential; True Love Waits finally here</li>
</ul>

<h3>Live Videos &amp; Documents</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s_Q7FoM-8ow">In Rainbows: From the Basement</a> - whole album live in a studio; essential entry point ✅</li>
