  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kid_A_Mnesia">Kid A Mnesia</a> - Kid A + Amnesiac reissued with third disc; Follow Me Around finally here</li>
  <li><a href="https://kida-mnesia.com/">Kid A Mnesia Exhibition</a> - free PC/Mac/PS5 experience; walk through the Kid A + Amnesiac artwork ✅</li>
</ul>

<h2>Dead &amp; Lost</h2>
<p>Sites that existed, that people used. Listed here so they're not forgotten.</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>ateaseweb.com/board</code> - the message board; ~20k daily visitors at its peak; died August 2024 ❌</li>
  <li><code>mortigitempo.com</code> - Green Plastic's message board; more welcoming than At Ease; gone ❌</li>
  <li><code>58hours.com</code> - gig database with world-map interface; the canonical setlist source for years; gone ~2022 ❌</li>
  <li><code>msgboard.radiohead.com</code> - official band board; still resolves but overrun by spam ⚠️</li>
  <li><code>followmearound.com</code> - the fan campaign that worked; "Follow Me Around" finally appeared on Kid A Mnesia; site gone ❌</li>
  <li><code>injektilo.com</code> - early FTP live-show host, absorbed into Green Plastic ~1999 ❌ <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/*/injektilo.com">Wayback only</a></li>
  <li><code>lift</code> - Jonathan Moore's early fansite; facsimile preserved in <a href="https://www.greenplastic.info/cold-storage/">Green Plastic Cold Storage</a> ❌</li>
  <li>Planet Telex / Wasteland / FADE OUT / Tony's Page - named on Site 1's links page as the key mid-90s fan hubs; all gone ❌</li>
  <li>Sites 5, 6, 11 - dead 404 ❌</li>
</ul>

